article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. -- — Ali Abdou Dibba had 17 points in Southern Illinois' 69-44 win against North Dakota State on Monday night. Dibba also added seven rebounds for the Salukis (2-2). Jarrett Hensley and Kennard Davis scored nine points apiece. Jacari White led the way for the Bison (2-3) with nine points and four assists. Brennan Watkins added eight points. Southern Illinois took the lead with 18:40 left in the first half and did not relinquish it. The score was 34-23 at halftime. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
